      description:
        "IMOS Ship of Opportunity Underway Expendable Bathythermographs (XBT) group is a research and data collection project working within the IMOS Ship of Opportunity Multi-Disciplinary Underway Network sub-facility.\n\nFive major (HRX) high-resolution XBT lines provide boundary to boundary profiling and closely spaced sampling to resolve mesoscale eddies, fronts and boundary currents.  The lines are repeated 4 times per year by an on-board technician.  The routes sample each major boundary current system using available commercial vessel traffic.  All of the transects transmit data in real-time.",
